Method Detail

getPitchesWithoutHarmonicsIn

public java.util.List<java.lang.Double> getPitchesWithoutHarmonicsIn(Sample.PitchUnit unit,
                                                                     double errorPercentage)
Returns a list of non harmonic frequencies. This function only makes sense on polyphonic pitch samples.

Parameters:
unit -
errorPercentage - defines the limits of what is seen as a harmonic. The list [100Hz,202Hz,230Hz] is reduced to [100Hz,230Hz] if the error percentage is greater than or equal to 2% (0.02)
Returns:
a reduced list without harmonics
